      <section eId="sec_46_8_311">
        <num>46-8-311</num>
        <content>
          <p>When any person is sued as the lessee of a railroad, service of a petition, summons, or other process may be effected by delivering a copy thereof to the depot agent or other officer of such lessee in the county where the action is pending, or by leaving a copy at the place where the usual and ordinary public business of such lessee in said county is transacted.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1884-85, p. 49, ยง 2; Civil Code 1895, ยง 2336; Civil Code 1910, ยง 2800; Code 1933, ยง 94-1103.)</p>
